<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1300" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1300">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/10618.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">O’Shaughnessy</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 20, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Consul at Progreso telegraphs as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>January 14. Mexican de facto authorities in the name of President
                                    called all the merchants and private landowners to the
                                    Government offices and required immediately sixty day loans for
                                    the purpose carrying on the northern campaign. Foreigners being
                                    obliged to contribute same as Mexicans practically enforced
                                    because of fear damage business if refused. Progreso
                                    contributions approximately thirty thousand pesos.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>